--- /dev/null
+++ b/docs/expose-upload-testing.md
@@ -0,0 +1,88 @@
+# Exposé Upload Testing
+
+Run manual checks in a current Chromium, Firefox, or Safari browser. Start the
+application from `app/` with `npm run dev`.
+
+## Happy path
+
+1. Open `/exposes/new`.
+2. Complete every field with valid data.
+3. Add one supported image and continue to the preview.
+4. Verify title, address, price, facts, description, and image count.
+5. Select **Publish listing** once.
+6. Confirm the detail route opens and identifies the entry as browser-local.
+7. Reload the page and confirm the listing remains available.
+8. Confirm it appears in `/exposes` and `/my-exposes`.
+9. Select its city in the search control and confirm the listing remains in the
+   filtered results.
+
+Repeat with eight images. Reorder them, choose a different cover, and verify the
+card cover and detail gallery order.
+
+## Validation matrix
+
+| Scenario | Expected result |
+| --- | --- |
+| Title shorter than 8 characters | Basics step remains open with an error |
+| Address without a comma or city | Complete-address error is shown |
+| Description shorter than 40 characters | Description error is shown |
+| Empty, negative, zero, or excessive numeric values | Relevant detail field shows its range |
+| Availability before today | Date error is shown |
+| No image | Images step cannot continue |
+| JPG, PNG, or WebP at or below 5 MB | Preview is added |
+| Unsupported file such as PDF or GIF | File is rejected with an error |
+| Image above 5 MB | File is rejected with its filename |
+| More than 8 images | Only available slots are filled and an error is shown |
+
+## Image interaction
+
+- Drop files onto the upload target and select files with the native picker.
+- Move images in both directions and verify the visual order.
+- Use **Set as cover** and verify that image moves to the first position.
+- Remove the cover and verify the next image becomes the cover.
+- Operate every image control using only the keyboard.
+- Confirm control labels are announced by a screen reader.
+
+## Persistence and deletion
+
+1. Publish two listings with different cities and identical titles.
+2. Confirm they receive distinct detail URLs.
+3. Open a second tab and confirm both entries load.
+4. Delete one entry from `/my-exposes` and cancel the first confirmation.
+5. Repeat and accept the confirmation.
+6. Confirm it disappears from My listings, results, search cities when no other
+   property uses that city, and its direct detail URL.
+7. Confirm static JSON properties cannot be deleted.
+
+To test unavailable storage, disable site storage in browser developer tools or
+use a restricted privacy context. Static entries should remain visible and the
+page should show a local-storage warning.
+
+To test quota handling, publish large image sets until the browser rejects a
+write. The form must stay on the preview step and display a suggestion to remove
+a listing or use smaller images.
+
+## Responsive and accessibility checks
+
+Test widths near 320 px, 768 px, and 1280 px:
+
+- Navigation and action links remain usable without horizontal page overflow.
+- Form columns collapse to one column on small screens.
+- Image cards and preview content remain readable.
+- Gallery thumbnails scroll horizontally rather than stretching the page.
+- Focus indicators are visible on links, buttons, inputs, and image controls.
+- Step progress exposes the active step through `aria-current`.
+- Loading, upload, publication, storage, and deletion errors are announced.
+- Disabled publication and deletion controls cannot be activated repeatedly.
+
+## Automated project checks
+
+From `app/`, run:
+
+```bash
+npm run lint
+npm run build
+```
+
+Treat TypeScript, ESLint, or Vite compilation errors as failures. A Node version
+warning alone is acceptable only when compilation and bundling still succeed.
