+╚══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╝
+```
+
+Estate Scout42 supports creating rental-property listings directly in the
+browser. The feature is intended for the demo application and does not require
+an account or backend service.
+
+![Image upload step in the property listing form](assets/expose-upload-lifecycle.png)
+
+## Opening the upload flow
+
+Use **List property** in the navigation or open `/exposes/new`. The form is
+split into four steps so validation feedback stays close to the relevant
+fields:
+
+1. **Basics** collects the title, property type, complete address, and
+   description.
+2. **Details** collects rent, area, rooms, floor, availability, pet policy, and
+   internet speed.
+3. **Images** accepts and arranges the property photos.
+4. **Preview** presents the resulting listing before publication.
+
+The Back button preserves all entered values. Cancel returns to the property
+results without storing a listing. Publication only happens from the final
+preview step.
+
+## Field validation
+
+All fields from the shared `Property` interface are required. The form applies
+the following rules:
+
+- Titles require at least 8 characters and allow up to 100.
+- Addresses require a street section and a comma-separated city section.
+- Descriptions require at least 40 characters and allow up to 1,500.
+- Warm rent, living space, rooms, floor, and internet speed must be positive
+  numbers within the ranges shown by validation errors. Ground floor uses `0`.
+- The availability date must be today or later.
+- Pet permission is represented by a checkbox.
+
+Validation runs before moving to the next step. Invalid fields remain on the
+current step and show an English error message.
+
+## Image handling
+
+Each listing requires between 1 and 8 images. Supported formats are JPEG, PNG,
+and WebP, with a maximum size of 5 MB per image.
+
+Images can be selected through the file picker or dropped on the upload area.
+Every accepted image receives a preview and controls to:
+
+- move it left or right in the gallery;
+- set it as the cover image;
+- remove it before publication.
+
+The first image is always the cover image used in search results. The remaining
+order is preserved in the detail-page gallery. Unsupported, oversized, and
+excess files are rejected with an accessible error message.
+
+## After publication
+
+A successful publication redirects to the new detail page. The listing also
+appears immediately:
+
+- in the main property results;
+- in city filtering when its city is selected;
+- under `/my-exposes`.
+
+Use **My listings** to see entries created in the current browser and delete an
+entry. Deletion requires confirmation and does not affect the static records in
+`app/data/exposes.json`.
+
+## Browser-local limitation
+
+Uploaded listings are available only in the browser profile that created them.
